                            <comment id="17890562" author="maedhroz" created="Thu, 17 Oct 2024 21:03:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After some conversation w/ &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;ve posted a patch that ensures &lt;tt&gt;EpochAwareDebounce&lt;/tt&gt; does not accept requests after it has been closed. This should avoid a situation where we cancel the current future during shutdown but then create a new one that is never cancelled and keeps a &lt;tt&gt;Stage&lt;/tt&gt; thread alive indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17890997" author="beobal" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2024 15:39:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not convinced that this fully addresses the problem. I agree with your analysis and the essence of your fix but I believe there&apos;s another case which can cause these timeouts and in fact I&apos;m still seeing intermittent failures with your patch applied, though less often.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What I think is sometimes happening in the test is that one node issues a request to another which is already shutting down. This request cannot be served but the issuer will wait on it for up to &lt;tt&gt;cms_await_timeout&lt;/tt&gt; (current default is 120s).&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve pushed a branch &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/beobal/cassandra/commits/samt/CASSANDRA-19848&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; which adds a tracker for the inflight futures, so we can cancel them all directly when closing. I would expect there to never be more than a handful of requests active at any time (these are debounced after all) but for safety, the tracker is bounded in size and automatically expires entries.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17891001" author="maedhroz" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2024 15:55:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve integrated &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=samt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;samt&quot;&gt;samt&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s fixes and gotten another 4 clean CI runs. I think we should be ready to go...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17891017" author="beobal" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2024 16:29:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
